.TH "NAVIGATION.TRANSITION" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Navigation.transition \- Navigation: transition property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]transition\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Navigation\f[R] interface returns a
\f[CR]NavigationTransition\f[R] object representing the status of an
in\-progress navigation, which can be used to track it.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]NavigationTransition\f[R] object, or \f[CR]null\f[R] if no
navigation is currently in progress.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] handleTransition() {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (navigation.transition) {
    showLoadingSpinner();
    \f[B]await\f[R] navigation.transition.finished;
    hideLoadingSpinner();
  }
}
.EE
